Or again, is not the naturalist or the botanist brought, by an easy stage, (happy man !), into a world of interest so absorbing, that he recks not of the fact, that yonder spire on the horizon marks his village-home, or that yonder diffused 'atmos- phere of distant smoke shrouds the manufacturing town, where he left the murky scene of his daily toil‚ by train, an hour ago?
